tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and low urine specific gravity, suggesting impaired renal function. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) may indicate urinary tract pathology, but no evidence of infection (negative nitrite/leukocytes). Glycosuria and ketonuria are present despite normal blood glucose and low HbA1c, possibly reflecting renal glycosuria or transient metabolic disturbance. Recommend further renal evaluation and clinical correlation for possible chronic kidney disease and to rule out other causes of abnormal urine findings.
